We need to show `n.choose k ≤ n^k / k!`
Multiplying both sides by `k!` (which is positive), we get:
`n.choose k * k! ≤ n^k`
But `n.choose k * k! = n! / (n-k)!` (this is the definition of binomial coefficient times factorial)
So we need to show `n! / (n-k)! ≤ n^k`
As mentioned earlier, `n! / (n-k)! = n × (n-1) × ... × (n-k+1)`
And `n × (n-1) × ... × (n-k+1) ≤ n × n × ... × n = n^k` (k times)
So the inequality is true.

